        <h1>üèîÔ∏è Serene Mountain Lake</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/600/400?random=1" alt="Serene Mountain Lake" width="600" height="400">
            <figcaption><strong>Mountain Lake Reflection</strong> - Captured at sunrise</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <article>
            <h2>About This Image</h2>
            <p>This <strong>breathtaking photograph</strong> captures the <em>perfect tranquility</em> of a mountain lake at dawn. The still waters create a <mark>mirror-like reflection</mark> of the surrounding peaks.</p>
            
            <h3>Technical Details</h3>
            <dl>
                <dt><strong>Location:</strong></dt>
                <dd>Rocky Mountain National Park</dd>
                <dt><strong>Time:</strong></dt>
                <dd><time datetime="06:30">6:30 AM</time></dd>
                <dt><strong>Season:</strong></dt>
                <dd>Early Summer</dd>
                <dt><strong>Weather:</strong></dt>
                <dd>Clear skies, <sup>22</sup>¬∞C</dd>
            </dl>

            <h4>Photography Notes</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Technique:</strong> Long exposure for smooth water</li>
                <li><em>Composition:</em> Rule of thirds applied</li>
                <li><u>Focus:</u> Hyperfocal distance for maximum sharpness</li>
                <li><mark>Special:</mark> Golden hour lighting</li>
            </ul>

            <blockquote>
                <p><i>"In every walk with nature, one receives far more than they seek."</i></p>
                <cite>~ John Muir</cite>
            </blockquote>
        </article>

