    </header>

    <main>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/600/400?random=2" alt="Golden Sunset Beach" width="600" height="400">
            <figcaption><strong>Beach Sunset</strong> - <em>Nature's daily masterpiece</em></figcaption>
        </figure>

        <article>
            <h2>Sunset Paradise</h2>
            <p>This <b>magnificent sunset</b> was captured during the <mark>golden hour</mark> when the sun kisses the horizon. The <i>warm colors</i> reflect beautifully on the wet sand and gentle waves.</p>

            <section>
                <h3>Color Analysis</h3>
                <table border="1">
                    <caption>Sunset Color Palette</caption>
                    <colgroup>
                        <col span="2">
                        <col>
                    </colgroup>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Color</th>
                            <th>Sky %</th>
                            <th>Water %</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Orange</strong></td>
                            <td>40%</td>
                            <td>20%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><em>Pink</em></td>
                            <td>30%</td>
                            <td>15%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><u>Purple</u></td>
                            <td>20%</td>
                            <td>10%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Blue</td>
                            <td>10%</td>
                            <td>55%</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </section>

            <h4>Beach Facts</h4>
            <p>Did you know that beaches are formed by <del>rivers</del> <ins>wave action</ins> over thousands of years? The sand composition tells the story of <sup>geological</sup> processes.</p>

            <pre>
Beach Formation Process:
1. Rock erosion by waves
2. Sediment transport
3. Deposition in coastal areas
4. Continuous reshaping
            </pre>
        </article>

        <section>
