        <h1>üå≤ Mystical Forest Path</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/600/400?random=3" alt="Mystical Forest Path" width="600" height="400">
            <figcaption><strong>Forest Trail</strong> - A path through ancient woods</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <article>
            <header>
                <h2>Journey Into Mystery</h2>
                <p><em>Follow the winding path</em> through this <strong>enchanted forest</strong> where sunlight filters through the canopy creating a <mark>magical atmosphere</mark>.</p>
            </header>

            <section>
                <h3>Forest Ecosystem</h3>
                <p>This forest represents a <b>complex ecosystem</b> where various species coexist. The <i>dappled light</i> supports different layers of vegetation.</p>

                <h4>Forest Layers</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Canopy Layer</strong> - Tallest trees forming the roof</li>
                    <li><em>Understory</em> - Mid-level shrubs and small trees</li>
                    <li><u>Forest Floor</u> - Ground level with decomposing matter</li>
                    <li><mark>Root Layer</mark> - Underground network</li>
                </ol>

                <h5>Wildlife Inhabitants</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Various bird species including <strong>woodpeckers</strong></li>
                    <li>Small mammals like <em>squirrels</em> and <i>chipmunks</i></li>
                    <li>Insects providing <u>pollination services</u></li>
                    <li><del>Large predators</del> <ins>Occasional deer sightings</ins></li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <aside>
                <h4>Photography Challenge</h4>
                <p>Capturing forest scenes requires understanding of:</p>
                <dl>
                    <dt><strong>Light Management:</strong></dt>
                    <dd>Dealing with high contrast between bright and dark areas</dd>
                    <dt><em>Composition:</em></dt>
                    <dd>Using leading lines like this path to guide the viewer's eye</dd>
                    <dt><u>Depth of Field:</u></dt>
                    <dd>Balancing foreground and background sharpness</dd>
                </dl>
            </aside>

            <blockquote cite="https://example.com/forest-quotes">
                <p><i>"The clearest way into the Universe is through a forest wilderness."</i></p>
                <cite>~ John Muir</cite>
            </blockquote>

            <section>
                <h4>Technical Information</h4>
                <table border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
                    <caption>Camera Settings Used</caption>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Setting</th>
                            <th scope="col">Value</th>
                            <th scope="col">Purpose</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Aperture</th>
                            <td>f/8</td>
                            <td>Optimal sharpness</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Shutter Speed</th>
                            <td>1/60<sup>th</sup> sec</td>
                            <td>Handheld stability</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">ISO</th>
                            <td>400</td>
                            <td>Low-light compensation</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </section>
        </article>

        <section>
            <h3>Forest Conservation</h3>
            <p>Protecting our forests is crucial for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Climate regulation</strong> through carbon absorption</li>
                <li><em>Biodiversity preservation</em> for countless species</li>
                <li><i>Water cycle maintenance</i> and soil protection</li>
                <li><mark>Recreational opportunities</mark> for future generations</li>
            </ul>

